post_text: Shelby County Schools is proud to announce and congratulate Dr. Lewis Brooks on being honored as a recipient of the NSPRA Superintendents to Watch for 2020 Award.
shared_text:
National School Public Relations Association
September 2 at 9:08 AM ·

NSPRA is pleased to announce the 2020 Superintendents to Watch. These 24 district leaders were selected for their use of communication technology in innovative and effective ways. They engage and inform their school communities with new communication technology tools combined with tried-and-true techniques.

These honorees have fewer than five years of experience as a superintendent of schools in a school district/ school board system and possess dynamic, fast-paced leadership with strong communication at its core. https://www.nspra.org/superintendents-watch

post_text: Farewell and best wishes to Assistant Superintendent of Human Resources Jim Miller on his well-deserved retirement from the Shelby County School District. Mr. Miller was honored at the board meeting last night and then again today. His retirement party theme is a nod to his favorite “imaginary camp” where life is always full of fun and games! We wish you nothing but fun times as you embark on this new adventure!

post_text: The Shelby County Chamber recently honored several Shelby County Schools employees during their 6th annual Healthcare Professional Awards ceremony. Treasa Daly - Nurse Supervisor for Shelby County Schools, Andrea Maddox - Health Sciences teacher at Chelsea High School, Elayne McCrimon - school nurse at Shelby County High School, and Michael Shields - Health Sciences teacher and athletic trainer at Helena High School, were honored as nominees for the award during a virtual awards ceremony held by the Chamber on August 26. See the story post below for more details.

post_text:
Some Shelby County Schools students could be eligible to receive free high-speed internet service through the Alabama Broadband Connectivity for Students Program. Look for the letter sometime after August 24 (see the example pictures of the envelope and sample letter). The letter will have your prepaid voucher number, which you can use for free high-speed internet service through December 30, 2020, and a list of internet service providers that you can call to set up your service.

For general questions about the ABC for Students program, please visit abcstudents.org.

post_text: Way to go Eli! We are so happy that you have fought so hard and met your goal of returning to school! #EliStrong
shared_text:
Leisha Florence Hairston shared a photo to the group: Praying for Eli.
August 17 at 8:02 AM ·

Thank you so much to Hillary Simon ❤️❤️❤️

https://www.cbs42.com/news/chelseas-eli-hairston-continues-recovery-9-months-after-traumatic-brain-injury/

Hillary Simon CBS42
August 17 at 7:50 AM ·

This guy inspires me. Meet Eli Hairston. He suffered a traumatic brain injury in November. He was in a coma, suffered multiple strokes, and had to relearn how to walk and talk. 9 months later, I sat down with him and his parents on how his road to recovery is going. Probably the most positive person I have met. You got this Eli 💪#prayforeli #elistrong

Praying for Eli

FULL STORY --> https://www.cbs42.com/news/chelseas-eli-hairston-continues-recovery-9-months-after-traumatic-brain-injury/

shared_text:
Ra'Netta Moore Underwood is with Tammy Moore and 10 others.
August 14 at 7:47 AM ·

I'm not crying, you're crying 😭

Just saw my oldest baby off to middle school, MIDDLE SCHOOL 😢

I'm sooooo proud of this young lady, words can't even explain.

She's my rock and Kenzie's 2nd momma. She's always there to lend a helping hand when I need her and I'm sooo thankful God chose me to be her mother!

I'm BEYOND BLESSED to call her my own!

God, please protect my daughter from any hurt, harm or danger as she boldly continues her education on school grounds during this pandemic! Equip her with the knowledge, tenacity and steadfastness she needs to succeed during this school year! May she continue to be leader and a good steward of her time! Protect those around her and help them all too encourage each other when things get a little tough! I plead the blood of Jesus over my child, YOUR child Lord! Amen!!!

6th grade, here comes Markiyah!!!

#SheIsHerDaddysTwin #IHaveABEAUTIFULDaughter #ImTheMomOfAMiddleSchooler
#shelbyfirstday

post_text: The first day of school for K-Z students at Mt Laurel Elementary was over before it ever began due to a power outage in the community. While some students were disappointed, other students - like Drew- thought it was the “best first day of school ever!” Principal Celita Deem said she wants to thank parents and students for their patience and understanding of the situation. “Everyone had great attitudes and were very nice.” 🥰 #shelbyfirstday

🎵 All in the Music Family!!🎵
Helena Band Director, Jeff Burnside, is kicking off his 33 year of teaching with several familiar faces! His daughter, Kaitlyn Traylor, is the music teacher at Forest Oaks and Wilsonville Elementary Schools. His son-in-law, Brenton Traylor, is the Assitant Band Director at Helena High School and his daughter-in-law, Katie Burnside, is the new Band Director at Helena Middle School. #shelbyfirstday

post_text: Gabriel, a kindergarten student at Wilsonville Elementary, was fearless on his #shelbyfirstday!
shared_text:
Sierra Gothard
August 13 at 11:42 AM ·

It took me so long to make the decision to send Gabriel to school. This is his Kindergarten year, it’s scary and exciting anyway, now there’s COVID-19 to make it that much scarier (for me, he couldn’t care less). Today, I dropped him off for his first day, and he didn’t even give me a chance to hug him 😭😥 Barely even a “Bye, Mommy.” He got out of the car and ran to his teachers. And I got home and cried. Why do they grow so fast?
#shelbyfirstday #wilsonvilleelementary #wes

#shelbyfirstday.
11th, 6th, 3rd, and 1st grade for my big guys.

Patrick drove himself, but left before I could make his pic driving away. So, I stalked him to the school and took a pic of his truck in the lot instead.

Abigail was attacked at the drop off and we didn’t get a pic of her walking in to her first day of middle school. But, thanks to Ms. Danielle, she got her pic made in the gym!

Annalee and Livy Claire were blinded by the sun and Bloom and Mr. Keith’s bright smiles this morning.

I guess it’s as good a day as any to start school...

* stay tuned for Jameson’s first day of 3k on September 8th.

shared_text:
Rick Karle WVTM 13
July 29 at 4:48 PM ·

Taelen Carter is a good kid.
Quiet by nature, Taelen loves his family and he loves his music- he’s a member of the Oak Mountain High School Band.
I hear he plays a mean snare drum.
For months now, Taelen’s bandmates have been there for him.

It was today when Taelen heard his doorbell ring- he answered the door, only to see several uniformed Birmingham Police officers smiling back at him.

You see, today, Taelen Carter turns sixteen, eighteen months after his father, Birmingham Police Sgt. WyTasha Carter, was gunned down and murdered in the line of duty.

Sunday, January 13th, 2019 seems like yesterday to Taelen.
Then again, it seems like a long time ago.

While Taelen wishes that he had his dad by his side while he celebrates his birthday, he’s truly appreciative of his father’s comrades who took time to cheer up his day.

Let’s wish Taelen a happy sixteenth, and give our best to Taelen’s mom Tiphanie and his sister Dashae.
I know our support will mean the world to them.

Birmingham Police Department, Alabama WVTM 13

shared_text:
Shelby County Career Tech
April 30 at 1:31 PM ·

Meet Jazmine Fitts

Jazmine is a senior at Montevallo High School. During her four years, she maintained good grades.
While focusing on academics, Jazmine was also actively involved in several extracurricular activities.
During her freshman year, she ran track, played volleyball and basketball.

Through the years, she was affiliated with the following student organizations: Family, Career and
Community Leaders of America (FCCLA), Future Business Leaders of America (FBLA), Student
Government Association (SGA) and the Montevallo WDOG Spotlight.

Jazmine plans to enlist in the military (Army) after high school graduation.

Shelby County Career Tech
April 24 at 8:47 AM ·

Meet Jaxon Butterworth, he is a 2020 graduate of Calera High School! Jaxon was a very active student in Mr. Forsythe’s carpentry class at Calera High School. Through his time in Mr. Forsythe’s class Jaxon knew he wanted to go into Construction Management. Jaxon is enrolled to go to Lawson State in the fall where he will study Construction Management and play baseball. Jaxon is also the recipient of the Alabama Home Builders Foundation scholarship. Congratulations Jaxon on all your accomplishments we all wish you the best!
#sccte #seniorshoutout #eagles #calerahigh

shared_text:
Shelby County Career Tech
April 24 at 8:56 AM ·

Meet Kelsey Mooney, Kelsey is a 2020 graduate of Helena High School and is headed to the University of Southern Mississippi on a full Academic Excellence Scholarship to study Athletic Training. Kelsey was the Vice-president of Helena High’s HOSA program. Kelsey competed in the HOSA State Leadership Conference in Sports Medicine and placed 3rd! Through Helena’s Sports Medicine program Kelsey also served her school as a student athletic trainer. We are so proud of Kelsey and wish her the best of luck at Southern Miss! Go Eagles! #scscte #seniorshoutout #helenahuskies #hosa

April 21 at 4:07 PM ·

Installment #1...
Senior Class of 2020....we have not forgotten you! Several sponsors donated funds so that we could purchase a personalized sign for each of you! These are all on display in front of the high school. I am going to post several pics and videos during the next few minutes. Please feel free to come get your sign when you can. All I ask is that you take a selfie with your sign or have someone take your picture holding it and send it to me either via email at bsnyder@shelbyed.org or tag the scwildcatnation account on instagram. We have another special tribute coming your way in the near future. Thank you to Scott Owen for making all of the signs. Thank you to the following people/groups for also sponsoring your signs: Alabama Graduation Products, Bob Patrick, Corley Ellis, Kevin Morris, Scott Owen, SCHS administrators, and SCHS Senior Class Sponsors. #scwildcatwatch #scproudprincipal
#outof👀notoutofmind
#stillplanning4graduation

Tricia Gober Crowe is with Russell Eugene Crowe at Shelby County AL Schools.
April 20 at 9:44 AM · Columbiana, AL ·

So proud of my girl Gracie Crowe. It saddens me that she is not likely to have the joy of experiencing Senior Prom, Senior Class Day or Graduation and only to receive her diploma in the mail. Although this isn't the ending she had hoped for, the end of senior year still means the start of something new. I love you Gracie Crowe, I believe in you wholeheartedly, the sky is the limit. Congratulations sweet girl, I am here for you today and always.
#ShelbySeniorShoutOut Calera High

post_text: We are proud to announce that Shelby County Schools has been named by NAMM as one of the nation’s 2020 Best Communities for Music Education. This award not only recognizes the dedication of music educators in all of our schools, but also commends the outstanding support of our Board Of Education, Superintendent, and communities. Congratulations to our Band, Choir, and Elementary Music teachers!! We are proud of your accomplishment!!
text: We are proud to announce that Shelby County Schools has been named by NAMM as one of the nation’s 2020 Best Communities for Music Education. This award not only recognizes the dedication of music educators in all of our schools, but also commends the outstanding support of our Board Of Education, Superintendent, and communities. Congratulations to our Band, Choir, and Elementary Music teachers!! We are proud of your accomplishment!!

shared_text:
Brianna Niven Whitehead
April 6 at 9:09 AM ·

#shelbyfirstdayback my shirt says, “Wake up. Teach Kids. Be Awesome.” This is for all of you, parents!! You are AWESOME and you’re teaching your kids SO MUCH right now!
This teacher is excited for a routine to be back to work and to get to finish the year with my fifth graders!!!

Remember to be patient with your family, friends, and school staff! We are in this TOGETHER!
Thank you, Shelby County Schools for investing in your teachers and students to make this transition smoother!
And to everyone- Wake up, teach kids (or grown ups😬), be AWESOME!
